Additional evaluation code:

episode_counts = [10, 50, 100, 200, 500, 1000]
win_rates = []

for n in episode_counts:
    wins = 0
    for _ in range(n):
        obs, _ = env.reset()
        done = False

        while not done:
            action = env.action_space.sample()
            obs, reward, terminated, truncated, _ = env.step(action)
            done = terminated or truncated

        wins += reward

    win_rates.append(wins / n)

plt.plot(episode_counts, win_rates, marker='o')
plt.xlabel("Evaluation Episodes")
plt.ylabel("Win Rate")
plt.title("Random Policy Win Rate")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

Around 500–1000 episodes are typically needed for a stable estimate of the random policy's win rate.


